ter>\n| <center>[[1986 Green Bay Packers season|Green Bay Packers]]</center> || (7) [[Fred Silva]] || (110) || || || || || (77) ||\n|}\n\n==Game summaries==\n\n====Week 1: at Dallas Cowboys====\n{{See also|1986 Dallas Cowboys season}}\n\nThe Giants had their first test in the opening week ''[[Monday Night Football]]'' game against the defending Eastern Division champion [[Dallas Cowboys]]. Playing in front of 59,804 fans at [[Texas Stadium]],<ref name=\"Cowboys\">Litsky, Frank. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50711FF3B5B0C7A8CDDA00894DE484D81 Cowboys Defeat Giants on Walker's Touchdown], ''The New York Times'', September 9, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> the Giants lost the opener, 31\u201328.<ref name=\"NYG1986\">[http://www.databasefootball.com/teams/teamyear.htm?tm=NYG&lg=nfl&yr=1986 1986 New York Giants] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070410044235/http://www.databasefootball.com/teams/teamyear.htm?tm=NYG&lg=nfl&yr=1986 |date=April 10, 2007 }}, databasefootball.com. accessed March 16, 2007.</ref> The teams played fairly evenly statistically; the Giants totalled 416&nbsp;yards to the Cowboys' 392.<ref>[http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=8&mth=9&yr=1986&tm=DAL&lg=NFL Box Score Giants Vs Cowboys 9/8/1986] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060526062854/http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=8&mth=9&yr=1986&tm=DAL&lg=NFL |date=May 26, 2006 }}, databasefootball.com, accessed May 20, 2007.</ref> Highlights of the game included Cowboys [[running back]] [[Herschel Walker]], in his first NFL game, rushing 10 times for 64&nbsp;yards and the game-winning touchdown, and fellow running back [[Tony Dorsett]] scoring on a 36-yard [[screen pass]] on the game's opening drive.<ref name=\"Cowboys\"/> The Giants struggled at the start of the game; they failed to get a [[first down]] on their first three drives, but their offense came alive and scored 28 points in the final three quarters.<ref name=\"Cowboys\"/>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle= {{NFLPrimaryStyle|New York Giants|year=1986|border=2}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 1: New York Giants at Dallas Cowboys\n |date=September 8, 1986\n |time=9:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EDT]]\n |road=Giants (0\u20131)\n |R1=0|R2=14|R3=7|R4=7|RT=28\n |home='''Cowboys (1\u20130)'''\n |H1=0|H2=17|H3=0|H4=14|HT=31\n |stadium=[[Texas Stadium]]\n |attendance=59,804\n |weather={{convert|71|F}}, relative humidity 71%, wind {{convert|11|mph|abbr=on}}\n |referee=[[Pat Haggerty (American football official)|Pat Haggerty]]\n |TV=[[Monday Night Football|ABC]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Al Michaels]] (play-by-play), [[Frank Gifford]] (color commentator)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198609080dal.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Giants|HomeName=Cowboys|state=collapsed}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=9:30\n| Team=Cowboys\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Tony Dorsett|Dorsett]]\n| QB=[[Danny White|White]]\n| yards=36\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Rafael Septien|Septien]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=7\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=6:21\n| Team=Cowboys\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Herschel Walker|Walker]]\n| yards=1\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Rafael Septien|Septien]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=14\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=1:49\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Bobby Johnson (American football)|Johnson]]\n| QB=[[Phil Simms|Simms]]\n| yards=13\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Bob Thomas (American football)|Thomas]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=14\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=0:25\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Stacy Robinson|Robinson]]\n| QB=[[Phil Simms|Simms]]\n| yards=3\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Bob Thomas (American football)|Thomas]]\n| Visitor=14\n| Home=14\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=0:00\n| Team=Cowboys\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=35\n| Kicker=[[Rafael Septien|Septien]]\n| Visitor=14\n| Home=17\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=2:15\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| yards=2\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Bob Thomas (American football)|Thomas]]\n| Visitor=21\n| Home=17\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=6:55\n| Team=Cowboys\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Tyson Chandler|Chandler]]\n| QB=[[Danny White|White]]\n| yards=1\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Rafael Septien|Septien]]\n| Visitor=21\n| Home=24\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=5:24\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Bobby Johnson (American football)|Johnson]]\n| QB=[[Phil Simms|Simms]]\n| yards=44\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Bob Thomas (American football)|Thomas]]\n| Visitor=28\n| Home=24\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=1:16\n| Team=Cowboys\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Herschel Walker|Walker]]\n| yards=10\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Rafael Septien|Septien]]\n| Visitor=28\n| Home=31\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEnd|Visitor=28|Home=31}}\n\n====Week 2: vs. San Diego Chargers====\n{{See also|1986 San Diego Chargers season}}\n \nIn week two, the Giants defeated the [[San Diego Chargers]] 20\u20137 in front of 74,921 fans at Giants Stadium.<ref name=\"Chargers\">Litsky, Frank. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F5071FF8355C0C768DDDA00894DE484D81 Giants' Defense Stifles Chargers], ''The New York Times'', September 15, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> The Giants led the Chargers 10\u20137 after three quarters before scoring 10 in the fourth quarter to put the game out of reach.<ref name=\"boxy\"/> [[Joe Morris (American football)|Joe Morris]] rushed 30 times for 83&nbsp;yards and [[defensive back]]s [[Terry Kinard]] and [[Kenny Hill (defensive back)|Kenny Hill]] intercepted two passes each.<ref name=\"Chargers\"/> Chargers quarterback [[Dan Fouts]] threw five second half interceptions. \"We took away their outside running game and their short passes\", Giants' [[defensive coordinator]] [[Bill Belichick]] said.<ref name=\"Chargers\"/> \"When Fouts tried to go deep, that's when we got interceptions.\"<ref name=\"Chargers\"/> The Giants dominated the Chargers in [[time of possession]]; 39 minutes 44 seconds to the Chargers' 20 minutes 16 seconds.<ref name=\"Chargers\"/> The Giants defense forced eight turnovers overall, and held the Chargers to 41 rushing yards on 13 carries.<ref name=\"boxy\">[http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=14&mth=9&yr=1986&tm=NYG&lg=NFL Box Score Chargers Vs Giants 9/14/1986] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070209052154/http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=14&mth=9&yr=1986&tm=NYG&lg=NFL |date=February 9, 2007 }}, databasefootball.com, accessed May 20, 2007.</ref> After the game Fouts complimented the Giants defense, \"There was no comparing the Giants' defense with the Dolphins' defense (the Chargers scored 50 points and totalled 500&nbsp;yards against the Dolphins in week one). We never got anything established against the Giants. Momma said there would be days like this, and she was right.\"<ref name=\"Chargers\"/>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|New York Giants|year=1986|border=2}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 2: San Diego Chargers at New York Giants\n |date=September 14, 1986\n |time=1:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EDT]]\n |road=Chargers (1\u20131)\n |R1=0|R2=7|R3=0|R4=0|RT=7\n |home='''Giants (1\u20131)'''\n |H1=3|H2=7|H3=0|H4=10|HT=20\n |stadium=[[Giants Stadium]]\n |attendance=74,921\n |weather={{convert|65|F}}, relative humidity 52%, wind {{convert|17|mph|abbr=on}}\n |referee=[[Fred Wyant]]\n |TV=[[NFL on NBC|NBC]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Don Criqui]] (play-by-play), [[Bob Trumpy]] (color commentator)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198609140nyg.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Chargers|HomeName=Giants|state=collapsed}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=6:10\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=21\n| Kicker=[[Joe Cooper (kicker)|Cooper]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=3\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=13:16\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| yards=1\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Joe Cooper (kicker)|Cooper]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=10\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=3:24\n| Team=Chargers\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Gary Anderson (running back)|Anderson]]\n| QB=[[Dan Fouts|Fouts]]\n| yards=29\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Rolf Benirschke|Benirschke]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=10\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=7:14\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Lionel Manuel|Manuel]]\n| QB=[[Phil Simms|Simms]]\n| yards=12\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Joe Cooper (kicker)|Cooper]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=17\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=3:12\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=20\n| Kicker=[[Joe Cooper (kicker)|Cooper]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=20\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEnd|Visitor=7|Home=20}}\n\n====Week 3: at Los Angeles Raiders====\n{{See also|1986 Los Angeles Raiders season}}\n\nThe Giants played the [[Los Angeles Raiders]] in Los Angeles in week three.<ref name=\"Raiders\">Litsky, Frank. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50716FE38540C718EDDA00894DE484D81 Giants Stop Raiders], ''The New York Times'', September 22, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> Joe Morris rushed for 110&nbsp;yards on 18 carries\u2014the first time in 19 games someone had rushed for 100&nbsp;yards against the Raiders\u2014and the Giants' defense held the Raiders to three [[Field goal (football)|field goals]].<ref name=\"Raiders\"/> Raiders running back [[Marcus Allen]] was held to 40&nbsp;yards on 15 carries, ending his then-NFL record 11 game 100&nbsp;yard rushing streak,<ref name=\"Raiders\"/> and the Giants defeated the Raiders 14\u20139. The Raiders gained a total of 58 rushing yards, and committed nine penalties.<ref name=\"Raidersbox\">[http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=21&mth=9&yr=1986&tm=LAD&lg=NFL Box Score Giants Vs Raiders] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060526063002/http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=21&mth=9&yr=1986&tm=LAD&lg=NFL |date=May 26, 2006 }}, databasefootball.com, accessed May 20, 2007.</ref> Raiders' quarterback [[Jim Plunkett]] completed 21 of 41 passes for 281&nbsp;yards, and Phil Simms threw touchdown passes of 18 and 11&nbsp;yards to [[wide receiver]] [[Lionel Manuel]].<ref name=\"Raiders\"/>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|New York Giants|year=1986|border=2}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 3: New York Giants at Los Angeles Raiders\n |date=September 21, 1986\n |time=4:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EDT]]\n |road='''Giants (2\u20131)'''\n |R1=0|R2=0|R3=7|R4=7|RT=14\n |home=Raiders (0\u20133)\n |H1=6|H2=0|H3=0|H4=3|HT=9\n |stadium=[[Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum]]\n |attendance=71,164\n |weather={{convert|63|F}}, relative humidity 