484D81 Giants' Rally to Beat Saints, 20\u201317], ''The New York Times'', September 29, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> They came back from a 17\u20130 second-quarter deficit, by scoring 20 points in the final three quarters.<ref name=\"Saints\"/> [[Rueben Mayes]] of the Saints returned the second-half kickoff 99&nbsp;yards for an apparent touchdown only to have the play called back because of an illegal block by linebacker [[Sam Mills]].<ref name=\"Saints\"/> The decisive points came on Phil Simms's 4-yard touchdown pass to tight end [[Zeke Mowatt]] midway through the fourth quarter.<ref name=\"Saints\"/> The Giants dominated the Saints in time of possession, holding the ball for 38 minutes and 47 seconds to the Saints 21 minutes and 13 seconds.<ref>[http://databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=28&mth=9&yr=1986&tm=NYG&lg=NFL Box Score Giants Vs Saints 9/28/1986] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060526063028/http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=28&mth=9&yr=1986&tm=NYG&lg=NFL |date=May 26, 2006 }}, databasefootball.com, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|New York Giants|year=1986|border=2}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 4: New Orleans Saints at New York Giants\n |date=September 28, 1986\n |time=1:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EDT]]\n |road=Saints (1\u20133)\n |R1=14|R2=3|R3=0|R4=0|RT=17\n |home='''Giants (3\u20131)'''\n |H1=0|H2=10|H3=3|H4=7|HT=20\n |stadium=[[Giants Stadium]]\n |attendance=72,769\n |weather={{convert|62|F}}, relative humidity 67%, wind {{convert|9|mph|abbr=on}}\n |referee=[[Bob Frederic]]\n |TV=[[NFL on CBS|CBS]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Dick Stockton]] (play-by-play), [[Dan Dierdorf]] (color commentator)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198609280nyg.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Saints|HomeName=Giants|state=collapsed}}\n{{AmF