n St. Louis in their fifth game of the season.<ref name=\"Morris\">Janofsky, Michael. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50711FA3D5A0C758CDDA90994DE484D81 Giants Triumph; Jets Win on Pass in Final Minute; Cardinals Lose, 13\u20136], ''The New York Times'', October 6, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> The Giants offense struggled, with Morris leading the team with a meager 53 rushing yards and quarterback [[Phil Simms]] completing only 8 of 20 passes for 104&nbsp;yards.<ref name=\"Morris\"/> Mark Bavaro caught two passes and Bobby Johnson caught two as well, for 55&nbsp;yards\u2014the only passes caught by a Giants' wide receiver.<ref name=\"Morris\"/> The game was a defensive struggle that featured 17 punts, four field goals (two by each team), and one touchdown.<ref name=\"Morris\"/> The Giants won 13\u20136, and the decisive score was a 1-yard touchdown run by Joe Morris early in the third quarter.<ref name=\"Morris\"/> The Giants defense held the Cardinals to 2.4&nbsp;yards per rush attempt and 3.8&nbsp;yards per pass attempt in the victory.<ref>[http://databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=5&mth=10&yr=1986&tm=SLC&lg=NFL Box Score Giants Vs Cardinals 10/5/1986] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060526063102/http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=5&mth=10&yr=1986&tm=SLC&lg=NFL |date=May 26, 2006 }}, databasefootball.com, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|New York Giants|year=1986|border=2}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 5: New York Giants at St. Louis Cardinals\n |date=October 5, 1986\n |time=1:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EDT]]\n |road='''Giants (4\u20131)'''\n |R1=0|R2=6|R3=7|R4=0|RT=13\n |home=Cardinals (0\u20135)\n |H1=3|H2=0|H3=3|H4=0|HT=9\n |stadium=[[Busch Stadium II|Busch Stadium]]\n |attendance=40,562\n |weather={{convert|60|F}}, relative humidity 70%, wind {{convert|11|mph|abb