the Giants defense sacked Eagles' quarterbacks [[Ron Jaworski]] and [[Randall Cunningham]] three times each.<ref name=\"Eagles\"/> The Giants won 35\u20133; their largest [[margin of victory]] since they defeated the Seattle Seahawks, 32\u20130, in 1981.<ref name=\"Eagles\"/> The Giants defense held the Eagles to 58 total yards,<ref name=\"Eaglesbox\">[http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=12&mth=10&yr=1986&tm=NYG&lg=NFL Box Score Eagles Vs Giants 10/12/1986] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100218203022/http://databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=12&mth=10&yr=1986&tm=NYG&lg=NFL |date=February 18, 2010 }}, databasefootball.com, accessed May 20, 2007.</ref> and Lawrence Taylor had four sacks and seven tackles. The sack total was Taylor's highest single game total since the 1984 season.<ref name=\"Eagles\"/> The Giants dominated in time of possession; they held the ball for 39 minutes and 33 seconds to the Eagles 20 minutes and 27 seconds.<ref name=\"Eaglesbox\"/> Simms completed 20 of 29 passes for 214&nbsp;yards and two touchdowns and ran for another touchdown.<ref name=\"Eagles\"/>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle= {{NFLPrimaryStyle|New York Giants|year=1986|border=2}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 6: Philadelphia Eagles at New York Giants\n |date=October 12, 1986\n |time=4:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EDT]]\n |road=Eagles (2\u20134)\n |R1=0|R2=3|R3=0|R4=0|RT=3\n |home='''Giants (5\u20131)'''\n |H1=0|H2=14|H3=14|H4=7|HT=35\n |stadium=[[Giants Stadium]]\n |attendance=74,221\n |weather={{convert|55|F}}, relative humidity 78%, wind {{convert|12|mph|abbr=on}}\n |referee=[[Jerry Markbreit]]\n |TV=[[NFL on CBS|CBS]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Dick Stockton]] (play-by-play), [[Dan Dierdorf]] (color commentator)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198610120nyg.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Eagles|Home