e?res=F50712FE3E5C0C718CDDAB0994DE484D81 One Quarter buys playoff ticket for Giants], ''The New York Times'', December 2, 1986. accessed March 26, 2007.</ref> In the win, Simms threw for nearly 400&nbsp;yards and wide receiver [[Stacy Robinson]] made an acrobatic catch at the goalline to set up the winning touchdown.<ref name=\"49ers\"/> Another important play also occurred during that ''Monday Night Football'' game. Here is a description of the play taken from a ''Monday Night Football'' broadcast in 2005: \"On Dec. 1 1986, New York Giants tight end Mark Bavaro cements his reputation as one of the toughest men in the NFL. With the Giants trailing, Bavaro catches an innocent pass from Phil Simms over the middle. It takes nearly seven 49ers defenders to finally drag him down, some of which are carried for almost 20&nbsp;yards, including future Hall of Famer [[Ronnie Lott]]. Bavaro's inspiring play jump starts the Giants, who win the game and eventually the Super Bowl.\"<ref>[http://media.espn.com/MediaZone/PressKits/NFL2005/MNF_list.htm MNF 36: The List Monday Night Football Special (Original Air Date: Aug. 25, 2005)], ESPN.com. accessed January 3, 2007.</ref>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle= {{NFLPrimaryStyle|New York Giants|year=1986|border=2}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 13: New York Giants at San Francisco 49ers\n |date=December 1, 1986\n |time=9:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EST]]\n |road='''Giants (11\u20132)'''\n |R1=0|R2=0|R3=21|R4=0|RT=21\n |home=49ers (7\u20135\u20131)\n |H1=3|H2=14|H3=0|H4=0|HT=17\n |stadium=[[Candlestick Park]]\n |attendance=59,777\n |weather={{convert|51|F}}, relative humidity 69%, wind {{convert|8|mph|abbr=on}}\n |referee=[[Ben Dreith]]\n |TV=[[Monday Night Football|ABC]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Al Michaels]] (play-by-play), [[Frank Gifford]] (color commentator)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198612010sfo.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{Am