ct.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50711F63F5B0C7B8CDDAB0994DE484D81 Alone at the Top: Giants Knock Out Redskins, 24\u201314; All Goes Wrong for Washington], ''The New York Times'', December 8, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> The Redskins held Joe Morris, who had rushed for 181&nbsp;yards in the Giants week eight victory, to 62&nbsp;yards on 22 carries.<ref name=\"Lead\"/> However, Lawrence Taylor recorded three sacks and harassed Redskins' quarterback [[Jay Schroeder]] all game, as the Giants recorded four sacks and the Redskins only recorded one.<ref name=\"Lead\"/> Phil Simms threw touchdown passes to Mark Bavaro, [[Bobby Johnson]], and Phil McConkey in the victory.<ref>Anderson, Dave. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50717FC355B0C7B8CDDAB0994DE484D81 Sports of the Times; Another Day in Surgery], ''The New York Times'', December 8, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> Schroeder threw six interceptions in the game, matching [[Sammy Baugh]]'s franchise record,<ref name=\"Lead\"/> and the Redskins had 7 [[Turnover (football)|turnovers]] overall.<ref>[http://databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=7&mth=12&yr=1986&tm=WAS&lg=NFL Box Score Giants Vs Redskins 12/7/1986] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060526063102/http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=7&mth=12&yr=1986&tm=WAS&lg=NFL |date=May 26, 2006 }}, databasefootball.com, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> After the game, Parcells gave the Redskins credit for their performance and told the reporters that he had a feeling that the two would meet again sometime in the playoffs.\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle= {{NFLPrimaryStyle|New York Giants|year=1986|border=2}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 14: New York Giants at Washington Redskins\n |date=December 7, 1986\n |time=1:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EST]]\n |road='''Giants (12\u20132)'''\n |R1=0|R2=14|R3=10|R4=0|RT=24\n |home=Redskins (11\u20133)\n |H1=0|H2=7|H3=0|H4=7|HT=14\n |stadium=[[RFK Stadium]]\n |attendance=55,642\n |weather={{convert|38|F}}, relative humidity 69%, wind {{convert|8|mph|abbr=on}}\n |referee=[[Red Cashion]]\n |TV=[[NFL on CBS|CBS]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Pat Summerall]] (play-by-play), [[John Madden (American football)|John Madden]] (color commentator), [[Irv Cross]] (sideline reporter)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198612070was.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Giants|HomeName=Redskins|state=collapsed}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=8:35\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Mark Bavaro|Bavaro]]\n| QB=[[Phil Simms|Simms]]\n| yards=9\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=0\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=1:55\n| Team=Redskins\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Kelvin Bryant|Bryant]]\n| yards=4\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Max Zendejas|Zendejas]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=7\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=0:23\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Bobby Johnson (American football)|Johnson]]\n| QB=[[Phil Simms|Simms]]\n| yards=7\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=14\n| Home=7\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=4:33\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=21\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=17\n| Home=7\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=3:11\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Phil McConkey|McConkey]]\n| QB=[[Phil Simms|Simms]]\n| yards=16\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=24\n| Home=7\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=3:24\n| Team=Redskins\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Kelvin Bryant|Bryant]]\n| QB=[[Jay Schroeder|Schroeder]]\n| yards=22\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Max Zendejas|Zendejas]]\n| Visitor=24\n| Home=14\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEnd|Visitor=24|Home=14}}\n\n====Week 15: vs. St. Louis Cardinals====\n{{See also|1986 St. Louis Cardinals (NFL) season}}\n\nThe Giants defeated the St. Louis Cardinals 27\u20137 in their fifteenth game of the season in front of 75,261 fans at Giants Stadium.<ref name=\"Rolling\">Litsky, Frank. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F5071EF634590C768DDDAB0994DE484D81 Giants Keep Rolling Around], ''The New York Times'', December 15, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> Joe Morris ran for 179&nbsp;yards and three touchdowns, but had three fumbles.<ref name=\"Rolling\"/> Phil Simms struggled, but the offense was effective nonetheless;<ref name=\"Rolling\"/> of the Giants 313 total yards, 252 came on the ground, while only 62 came from the passing game.<ref name=\"Simms62\">[http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=14&mth=12&yr=1986&tm=NYG&lg=NFL Box Score Cardinal Vs Giants 12/14/1986] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111122014853/http://databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=14&mth=12&yr=1986&tm=NYG&lg=NFL |date=November 22, 2011 }}, databasefootball.com, accessed May 20, 2007.</ref> The Giants defense controlled the Cardinals throughout the game, particularly in the first half; the Cardinals' first four possessions ended in third-down sacks and fourth-down punts.<ref name=\"Rolling\"/> The Giants committed only two penalties for a total of ten yards,<ref name=\"Simms62\"/> and their defense set a franchise record with nine sacks, despite sending Lawrence Taylor into pass coverage for most of the game.<ref name=\"Rolling\"/>  With the victory the Giants clinched their first NFC East division crown.\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|New York Giants|year=1986|border=2}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 15: St. Louis Cardinals at New York Giants\n |date=December 14, 1986\n |time=1:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EST]]\n |road=Cardinals (3\u201311\u20131)\n |R1=0|R2=0|R3=0|R4=7|RT=7\n |home='''Giants (13\u20132)'''\n |H1=7|H2=10|H3=3|H4=7|HT=27\n |stadium=[[Giants Stadium]]\n |attendance=75,261\n |weather={{convert|26|F}}, relative humidity 46%, wind {{convert|14|mph|abbr=on}}, wind chill {{convert|14|F}}\n |referee=[[Bob McElwee]]\n |TV=[[NFL on CBS|CBS]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Jack Buck]] (play-by-play), [[Joe Theismann]] (color commentator)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198612140nyg.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Cardinals|HomeName=Giants|state=collapsed}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=4:39\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| yards=2\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=7\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=3:29\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| yards=3\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=14\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=0:11\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=26\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=17\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=3:30\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=23\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=20\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=6:37\n| Team=Cardinals\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Roy Green|Green]]\n| QB=[[Stump Mitchell|Mitchell]]\n| yards=15\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Steve Schubert|Schubert]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=20\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=1:57\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| yards=1\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=27\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEnd|Visitor=7|Home=27}}\n\n====Week 16: vs. Green Bay Packers====\n{{See also|1986 Green Bay Packers season}}\n\nThe Giants headed into their final regular season game against the [[Green Bay Packers]] as 11\u00bd-point favorites and needed a victory to secure homefield advantage throughout the playoffs.<ref name=\"Home\">Litsky, Frank. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50712FE38540C738EDDAB0994DE484D81 Giants Seek Edge for Playoffs], ''The New York Times'', December 20, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> Sparked by a blocked punt returned for a TD by Tom Flynn, who had recently been picked up from the Packers, the Giants defeated the Packers 55\u201324 in front of 71,351 fans at Giants Stadium to finish the regular season with a franchise record 14 victories.<ref name=\"Packers\">Litsky, Frank. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50716F8385C0C728EDDAB0994DE484D81 Giants Stay Home for Playoffs], ''The New York Times'', December 21, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> The win was the Giants' ninth consecutive, matching the team record set in 1962.<ref name=\"Packers\"/> The Giants also set a franchise record for points in the first quarter of a game with 21.<ref name=\"Packers\"/> Although the Packers cut the score to 24\u201317 at halftime, the Giants scored 31 second half points to put the game out of reach.\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle= {{NFLPrimaryStyle|New York Giants|year=1986|border=2}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 16: Green Bay Packer