[[Texas Stadium]],<ref name=\"Cowboys\">Litsky, Frank. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50711FF3B5B0C7A8CDDA00894DE484D81 Cowboys Defeat Giants on Walker's Touchdown], ''The New York Times'', September 9, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> the Giants lost the opener, 31\u201328.<ref name=\"NYG1986\">[http://www.databasefootball.com/teams/teamyear.htm?tm=NYG&lg=nfl&yr=1986 1986 New York Giants] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070410044235/http://www.databasefootball.com/teams/teamyear.htm?tm=NYG&lg=nfl&yr=1986 |date=April 10, 2007 }}, databasefootball.com. accessed March 16, 2007.</ref> The teams played fairly evenly statistically; the Giants totalled 416&nbsp;yards to the Cowboys' 392.<ref>[http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=8&mth=9&yr=1986&tm=DAL&lg=NFL Box Score Giants Vs Cowboys 9/8/1986] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060526062854/http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=8&mth=9&yr=1986&tm=DAL&lg=NFL |date=May 26, 2006 }}, databasefootball.com, accessed May 20, 2007.</ref> Highlights of the game included Cowboys [[running back]] [[Herschel Walker]], in his first NFL game, rushing 10 times for 64&nbsp;yards and the game-winning touchdown, and fellow running back [[Tony Dorsett]] scoring on a 36-yard [[screen pass]] on the game's opening drive.<ref name=\"Cowboys\"/> The Giants struggled at the start of the game; they failed to get a [[first down]] on their first three drives, but their offense came alive and scored 28 points in the final three quarters.<ref name=\"Cowboys\"/>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle= {{NFLPrimaryColor|New York Giants}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 1: New York Giants at Dallas Cowboys\n |date=September 8, 1986\n |time=9:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EDT]]\n |road=Giants (0\u20131)\n |R1=0|R2=14|R3=7|R4=7|RT=28\n |home='''Cowboys (1\u20130)'''\n |H1=0|H2=17|H3=0|H4=14|HT=31\n 