s=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| yards=2\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Bob Thomas (American football)|Thomas]]\n| Visitor=21\n| Home=17\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=6:55\n| Team=Cowboys\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Tyson Chandler|Chandler]]\n| QB=[[Danny White|White]]\n| yards=1\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Rafael Septien|Septien]]\n| Visitor=21\n| Home=24\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=5:24\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Bobby Johnson (American football)|Johnson]]\n| QB=[[Phil Simms|Simms]]\n| yards=44\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Bob Thomas (American football)|Thomas]]\n| Visitor=28\n| Home=24\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=1:16\n| Team=Cowboys\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Herschel Walker|Walker]]\n| yards=10\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Rafael Septien|Septien]]\n| Visitor=28\n| Home=31\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEnd|Visitor=28|Home=31}}\n\n====Week 2: vs. San Diego Chargers====\n{{See also|1986 San Diego Chargers season}}\n \nIn week two, the Giants defeated the [[San Diego Chargers]] 20\u20137 in front of 74,921 fans at Giants Stadium.<ref name=\"Chargers\">Litsky, Frank. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F5071FF8355C0C768DDDA00894DE484D81 Giants' Defense Stifles Chargers], ''The New York Times'', September 15, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> The Giants led the Chargers 10\u20137 after three quarters before scoring 10 in the fourth quarter to put the game out of reach.<ref name=\"boxy\"/> [[Joe Morris (American football)|Joe Morris]] rushed 30 times for 83&nbsp;yards and [[defensive back]]s [[Terry Kinard]] and [[Kenny Hill (defensive back)|Kenny Hill]] intercepted two passes each.<ref name=\"Chargers\"/> Chargers quarterback [[Dan Fouts]] threw five second half interceptions. \"We took away their outside running game and their short passes\", Giants' [[defensive coordinator]] [[Bill Belichick]] said.<ref name=\"Chargers\"/> \"When Fouts tried to go deep, that's when we got interceptions.\"<ref name=\"Chargers\"/> The Giants dominated the Chargers in [[time of possession]]; 39 minutes 44 seconds to the Chargers' 20 minutes 16 seconds.<ref name=\"Chargers\"/> The Giants defense forced eight turnovers overall, and held the Chargers to 41 rushing yards on 13 carries.<ref name=\"boxy\">[http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=14&mth=9&yr=1986&tm=NYG&lg=NFL Box Score Chargers Vs Giants 9/14/1986] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070209052154/http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=14&mth=9&yr=1986&tm=NYG&lg=NFL |date=February 9, 2007 }}, databasefootball.com, accessed May 20, 2007.</ref> After the game Fouts complimented the Giants defense, \"There was no comparing the Giants' defense with the Dolphins' defense (the Chargers scored 50 points and totalled 500&nbsp;yards against the Dolphins in week one). We never got anything established against the Giants. Momma said there would be days like this, and she was right.\"<ref name=\"Chargers\"/>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryColor|New York Giants}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 2: San Diego Chargers at New York Giants\n |date=September 14, 1986\n |time=1:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EDT]]\n |road=Chargers (1\u20131)\n |R1=0|R2=7|R3=0|R4=0|RT=7\n |home='''Giants (1\u20131)'''\n |H1=3|H2=7|H3=0|H4=10|HT=20\n |stadium=[[Giants Stadium]]\n |attendance=74,921\n |weather={{convert|65|F}}, relative humidity 52%, wind {{convert|17|mph|abbr=on}}\n |referee=[[Fred Wyant]]\n |TV=[[NFL on NBC|NBC]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Don Criqui]] (play-by-play), [[Bob Trumpy]] (color commentator)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198609140nyg.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Chargers|HomeName=Giants|state=collapsed}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=6:10\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=21\n| Kicker=[[Joe Cooper (kicker)|Cooper]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=3\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=13:16\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Joe Morris (American football)|Morris]]\n| yards=1\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Joe Cooper (kicker)|Cooper]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=10\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=3:24\n| Team=Chargers\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Gary Anderson (running back)|Anderson]]\n| QB=[[Dan Fouts|Fouts]]\n| yards=29\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Rolf Benirschke|Benirschke]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=10\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=7:14\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Lionel Manuel|Manuel]]\n| QB=[[Phil Simms|Simms]]\n| yards=12\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Joe Cooper (kicker)|Cooper]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=17\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=3:12\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=20\n| Kicker=[[Joe Cooper (kicker)|Cooper]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=20\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEnd|Visitor=7|Home=20}}\n\n====Week 3: at Los Angeles Raiders====\n{{See also|1986 Los Angeles Raiders season}}\n\nThe Giants played the [[Los Angeles Raiders]] in Los Angeles in week three.<ref name=\"Raiders\">Litsky, Frank. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50716FE38540C718EDDA00894DE484D81 Giants Stop Raiders], ''The New York Times'', September 22, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> Joe Morris rushed for 110&nbsp;yards on 18 carries\u2014the first time in 19 games someone had rushed for 100&nbsp;yards against the Raiders\u2014and the Giants' defense held the Raiders to three [[Field goal (football)|field goals]].<ref name=\"Raiders\"/> Raiders running back [[Marcus Allen]] was held to 40&nbsp;yards on 15 carries, ending his then-NFL record 11 game 100&nbsp;yard rushing streak,<ref name=\"Raiders\"/> and the Giants defeated the Raiders 14\u20139. The Raiders gained a total of 58 rushing yards, and committed nine penalties.<ref name=\"Raidersbox\">[http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=21&mth=9&yr=1986&tm=LAD&lg=NFL Box Score Giants Vs Raiders] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060526063002/http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=21&mth=9&yr=1986&tm=LAD&lg=NFL |date=May 26, 2006 }}, databasefootball.com, accessed May 20, 2007.</ref> Raiders' quarterback [[Jim Plunkett]] completed 21 of 41 passes for 281&nbsp;yards, and Phil Simms threw touchdown passes of 18 and 11&nbsp;yards to [[wide receiver]] [[Lionel Manuel]].<ref name=\"Raiders\"/>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryColor|New York Giants}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 3: New York Giants at Los Angeles Raiders\n |date=September 21, 1986\n |time=4:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EDT]]\n |road='''Giants (2\u20131)'''\n |R1=0|R2=0|R3=7|R4=7|RT=14\n |home=Raiders (0\u20133)\n |H1=6|H2=0|H3=0|H4=3|HT=9\n |stadium=[[Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum]]\n |attendance=71,164\n |weather={{convert|63|F}}, relative humidity 76%, wind {{convert|11|mph|abbr=on}}\n |referee=[[Red Cashion]]\n |TV=[[NFL on CBS|CBS]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Pat Summerall]] (play-by-play), [[John Madden (American football)|John Madden]] (color commentator), [[Irv Cross]] (sideline reporter)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198609210rai.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Giants|HomeName=Raiders|state=collapsed}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=7:15\n| Team=Raiders\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=22\n| Kicker=[[Chris Bahr|Bahr]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=3\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=3:17\n| Team=Raiders\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=25\n| Kicker=[[Chris Bahr|Bahr]]\n| Visitor=0\n| Home=6\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=7:25\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Lionel Manuel|Manuel]]\n| QB=[[Phil Simms|Simms]]\n| yards=18\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Joe Cooper (kicker)|Cooper]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=6\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=12:22\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Lionel Manuel|Manuel]]\n| QB=[[Phil Simms|Simms]]\n| yards=11\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Joe Cooper (kicker)|Cooper]]\n| Visitor=14\n| Home=6\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=5:44\n| Team=Raiders\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=33\n| Kicker=[[Chris Bahr|Bahr]]\n| Visitor=14\n| Home=9\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEnd|Visitor=14|Home=9}}\n\n====Week 4: vs. New Orleans Saints====\n{{See also|1986 New Orleans Saints season}}\n\nThe Giants rallied to beat the [[New Orleans Saints]] 20\u201317 in front of 72,769 fans at Giants Stadium in week four.<ref name=\"Saints\">Litsky, Frank. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50714F7395A0C7A8EDDA00894DE484D81 Giants' Rally to Beat Saints, 20\u201317], ''The New York Times'', September 29, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> They came back from a 17\u20130 second quarter deficit, by scoring 20 points in the final three quarters.<ref name=\"Saints\"/> [[Rueben Mayes]] of the Saints returned the second half kickoff 99&nbsp;yards for an apparent touchdown only to have the play called back because of an illegal block by linebacker [[Sam Mills]].<ref name=\"Saints\"/> The decisive points came on Phil Simms's 4-yard touchdown pass to tight end [[Zeke Mowatt]] midway through the fourth quarter.<ref name=\"Saints\"/> The Giants dominated the Saints in time of possession, holding the ball for 38 minutes and 47 seconds to the Saints 21 minutes and 13 seconds.<ref>[http://databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=28&mth=9&yr=1986&tm=NYG&lg=NFL Box Score Giants Vs Saints 9/28/1986] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060526063028/http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=28&mth=9&yr=1986&tm=NYG&lg=NFL |date=May 26, 2006 }}, databasefootball.com, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryColor|New York Giants}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 4: New Orleans Saints at New York Giants\n |date=September 28, 1986\n |time=1:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EDT]]\n |road=Saints (1\u20133)\n |R1=14|R2=3|R3=0|R4=0|RT=17\n |home='''Giants (3\u20131)'''\n |H1=0|H2=10|H3=3|H4=7|HT=20\n |stadium=[[Giants Stadium]]\n |attendance=72,769\n |weather={{convert|62|F}}, relative humidity 67%, wind {{convert|9|mph|abbr=on}}\n |referee=[[Bob Frederic]]\n |TV=[[NFL on CBS|CBS]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Dick Stockton]] (play-by-play), [[Dan Dierdorf]] (color commentator)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198609280nyg.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Saints|HomeName=Giants|state=collapsed}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=12:00\n| Team=Saints\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Eric Martin (wide receiver)|Martin]]\n| QB=[[Dave Wilson (American football)|Wilson]]\n| yards=63\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Morten Andersen|Andersen]]\n| Visitor=7\n| Home=0\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=3:37\n| Team=Saints\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RushTD\n| Runner=[[Dalton Hilliard|Hilliard]]\n| yards=1\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Morten Andersen|Andersen]]\n| Visitor=14\n| Home=0\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=12:47\n| Team=Saints\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=27\n| Kicker=[[Morten Andersen|Andersen]]\n| Visitor=17\n| Home=0\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=7:10\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=29\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=17\n| Home=3\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=2\n| Time=1:20\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Mark Bavaro|Bavaro]]\n| QB=[[Phil Simms|Simms]]\n| yards=19\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=17\n| Home=10\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=3\n| Time=7:19\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=28\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=17\n| Home=13\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=4\n| Time=8:03\n| Team=Giants\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=RecTD\n| Receiver=[[Zeke Mowatt|Mowatt]]\n| QB=[[Phil Simms|Simms]]\n| yards=4\n| kickresult=good\n| Kicker=[[Raul Allegre|Allegre]]\n| Visitor=17\n| Home=20\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEnd|Visitor=17|Home=20}}\n\n====Week 5: at St. Louis Cardinals====\n{{See also|1986 St. Louis Cardinals (NFL) season}}\n\nThe Giants faced the [[St. Louis Cardinals (NFL)|St. Louis Cardinals]] in St. Louis in their fifth game of the season.<ref name=\"Morris\">Janofsky, Michael. [https://select.nytimes.com/search/restricted/article?res=F50711FA3D5A0C758CDDA90994DE484D81 Giants Triumph; Jets Win on Pass in Final Minute; Cardinals Lose, 13\u20136], ''The New York Times'', October 6, 1986, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref> The Giants offense struggled, with Morris leading the team with a meager 53 rushing yards and quarterback [[Phil Simms]] completing only 8 of 20 passes for 104&nbsp;yards.<ref name=\"Morris\"/> Mark Bavaro caught two passes and Bobby Johnson caught two as well, for 55&nbsp;yards\u2014the only passes caught by a Giants' wide receiver.<ref name=\"Morris\"/> The game was a defensive struggle that featured 17 punts, four field goals (two by each team), and one touchdown.<ref name=\"Morris\"/> The Giants won 13\u20136, and the decisive score was a 1-yard touchdown run by Joe Morris early in the third quarter.<ref name=\"Morris\"/> The Giants defense held the Cardinals to 2.4&nbsp;yards per rush attempt and 3.8&nbsp;yards per pass attempt in the victory.<ref>[http://databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=5&mth=10&yr=1986&tm=SLC&lg=NFL Box Score Giants Vs Cardinals 10/5/1986] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060526063102/http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=5&mth=10&yr=1986&tm=SLC&lg=NFL |date=May 26, 2006 }}, databasefootball.com, accessed May 17, 2007.</ref>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryColor|New York Giants}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week 5: New York Giants at St. Louis Cardinals\n |date=October 5, 1986\n |time=1:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EDT]]\n |road='''Giants (4\u20131)'''\n |R1=0|R2=6|R3=7|R4=0|RT=13\n |home=Cardinals (0\u20135)\n |H1=3|H2=0|H3=3|H4=0|HT=9\n |stadium=[[Busch Stadium II|Busch Stadium]]\n |attendance=40,562\n |weather={{convert|60|F}}, relative humidity 70%, wind {{convert|11|mph|abbr=on}}\n |referee=[[Chuck Heberling]]\n |TV=[[NFL on CBS|CBS]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Gary Bender]] (play-by-play), [[Hank Stram]] (color commentator)\n |reference=[https://www.pro-football-reference.com/boxscores/198610050crd.htm Box Score]\n |scoring=\n}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryStart|VisitorName=Giants|HomeName=Cardinals|state=collapsed}}\n{{AmFootballScoreSummaryEntry\n| Quarter=1\n| Time=8:37\n| Team=Cardinals\n| DrivePlays=\n| DriveLength=\n| DriveTime=\n| Type=FG\n| yards=31\n| Kicker=[[John Lee (placekicker)|Lee]]