icial)|Jim Poole]] || (90) [[Gil Mace]] || (82) [[Pat Mallette]] || || (115) [[Hendi Ancich]]\n|}\n\n====NFC Divisional Playoffs: vs. San Francisco 49ers====\n{{See also|1986 San Francisco 49ers season}}\n\nThe Giants defeated the San Francisco 49ers 49\u20133 in their opening playoff game.<ref name=\"Playoffs\">Litsky, Frank. [https://www.nytimes.com/1987/01/05/sports/giants-roll-over-49ers-and-on-to-nfc-final.html Giants Roll Over 49ers and on to N.F.C. Final], ''The New York Times'', January 5, 1987. accessed March 25, 2008.</ref> Favored by only three points, the Giants caught a break when 49ers WR Jerry Rice fumbled an apparent touchdown catch-and-carry off his knee early in the game, then dominated the Niners the rest of the way. Their defense held the 49ers to 29&nbsp;yards rushing, 184&nbsp;yards in total offense, and 2 of 14 on third-down conversions.<ref name=\"Playoffs\"/> The Giants did not commit a turnover and totalled 216 rushing yards.<ref name=\"Divisional\"/> Jim Burt knocked 49ers quarterback Joe Montana out of the game in the second quarter, hitting him as he threw a pass which Lawrence Taylor intercepted and returned the pick 34&nbsp;yards for a touchdown. The Giants defense also held the 49ers to only nine first downs, and 15 of 37 passing for zero touchdowns and three interceptions.<ref name=\"Divisional\">[http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=4&mth=1&yr=1987&tm=NYG&lg=NFL Box Score 49ers Vs Giants 1/4/1987] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060526062832/http://www.databasefootball.com/boxscores/gamedata.htm?dy=4&mth=1&yr=1987&tm=NYG&lg=NFL |date=May 26, 2006 }}, databasefootball.com, accessed May 20, 2007.</ref>\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle= {{NFLPrimaryColor|New York Giants}}; {{NFLSecondaryColor|New York Giants}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=1986 NFC Divisional Playoff: San Francisco 49ers at New York Giants\n |date=January 4, 1987\n |time=12:30 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EST]]\